projects.description:
The programme will contribute towards capacity development of local governments and their umbrella organisations in nine partner countries: Benin, Burundi, Ghana, Nicaragua, Rwanda, Uganda, the Palestinian territories, South Africa and South Sudan.  

Sustainable local economic development is hard to realise without an effectively functioning local government. The programme is aimed at improving the municipal conditions required for economic development. 

Ultimately, the program will help those local governments be in a better position to provide for: 

•food security;
•water management;
•the safety of their citizens and legal order;
•the sexual and reproductive health and rights of their citizens.

The purpose of the Local Government Capacity Programme is to enable partner countries, when it comes to dealing with these issues, to be better equipped in:

•developing and implementing policy;
•taking steps in the development process;
•adapting and modernising themselves in response to changing situations;
•cooperating with external parties;
•creating cohesion in their working methods.
